1.Theyâ€™re negative gamma â€˜both waysâ€™ â†’ very tough for amy MM to quote consistently on-chain (manage the implicit negative gamma + show their hands), even without insider flow.

2.The only sustainable model is strong 2-way liquidity on â€˜something closer to HLP-style poolsâ€™, where diversification benefits > toxic flow over time.

3.Opening auctions feel overkill if thereâ€™s a reliable oracle. 

Better path: deployers prove â€œskin in the gameâ€ by showing the liquidity they can commit/attract before going order book.

4.Cross-venue arb is critical. Most big events already trade elsewhere; infra should make arbitrage seamless, not siloed.

Binary markets on a HL style order book can be powerful but success depends on liquidity depth + arb pathways, not just the contract spec.
